// 21.905 — 🧪 NEW pin tests for loyalty-redemption + loyalty-tiers — sister of scc v13.9705 same-day port. `lib/__tests__/loyalty-redemption.test.ts` (28 tests on REDEMPTION_TIERS + eligibleRedemptionTiers + bestRedemptionTier + applyRedemptionTier — hard on the $75 cliff: 300-pt strict-less-than vs 400-pt inclusive — penny-rounding pinned at exact equality). `lib/__tests__/loyalty-tiers.test.ts` (16 tests on getTierProgress — Visitor/Regular/Local/Family placement, exact-threshold inclusive transitions, defensive NaN/negative inputs, top-tier toNext=null). 44 tests in ~525ms via Node 25 `--experimental-strip-types` (no test-runner dep added). NEW `pnpm test:all` script + `allowImportingTsExtensions: true` in tsconfig (required for explicit `.ts` import suffix the strip-types loader needs). glw's lib here is mirror-from-inv-SoT (used by `components/LoyaltyCard.tsx` + `app/order/OrderMenu.tsx`); the test pin defends against silent drift when the inv source-of-truth threshold math changes and the mirror update gets missed. tsc clean.
// 21.605 — 🛡️ JSON-LD `</script>` breakout escape wired at 5 missed call sites. `lib/json-ld-safe.ts` `safeJsonLd()` helper has existed since the v2.81-class port, but 5 places were still emitting JSON-LD via raw `JSON.stringify({...})` into `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` — the exact XSS sink the helper exists to prevent. Sites hardened: `app/page.tsx:1250` (HowTo JSON-LD), `app/apply/layout.tsx:55` (BreadcrumbList), `app/learn/page.tsx:151+174` (LearningResource + BreadcrumbList), `app/careers/page.tsx:99` (BreadcrumbList). Each now imports + uses `safeJsonLd()`. Threat model: if any of these JSON-LD payloads ever incorporates admin-edited or DB-sourced strings (blog titles, product copy, vendor names), a value containing `</script>` would break out of the script tag and inject HTML. Today's inputs are developer-hardcoded so real exploitability is near-zero; this is defense-in-depth so a future schema change (e.g. blog post titles in JSON-LD) doesn't silently introduce the vulnerability. Sister of cannagent v5.9085 ldJson() escape + GW already-fixed + scc v13.9505 same-day port. tsc clean.
// 21.505 — 🛡️ CSP-report receiver — fix silent-drop of oversize payloads. Pre-fix `app/api/csp-report/route.ts` capped payload at 4KB and tried to "repair" truncated JSON by appending `}}` after a `slice(0, 4096)`. That only produces valid JSON when truncation lands at the exact right nesting depth — in practice almost every oversize report parsed as malformed JSON, hit the catch block, and was silently dropped. Bumped cap to 16KB (covers real-shaped reports with long original-policy + source-file fields) and on oversize: log size class with `console.error("oversized payload dropped, size=X")` + return 204. Sister scc v13.9405 same-fix. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop cross-stack CSP-receiver audit.
