// 18.605 — 📧 Email preheader — added inbox-preview snippet to 3 transactional templates (welcome, order-confirmation, quiz-nurture). Pre-fix the inbox preview line shown BEFORE opening the email fell back to first visible body text — typically the brand boilerplate "${STORE.name} · Wenatchee since 2014" — instead of a hook. Hidden via `display:none;font-size:0;line-height:0;max-height:0;overflow:hidden;mso-hide:all;` so it doesn't render in the email body but Gmail/Apple Mail/Outlook all surface it as the inbox-preview snippet. Per-template copy: welcome → "Welcome … your account is set up. Tap to start shopping." order-confirm → "Order confirmed at … Pay cash on pickup. We'll text when ready." quiz-nurture → "Your strain match is ready — … from …". Customer-UX win on the most-visible inbox surface (preview line is the second-most-read line after subject). Sister scc v13.6305. GW deferred — `shell()` helper has no `<head>`/`<body>` structure, needs sig refactor to thread preheader per-template; T74-followup. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 74 round-3 dimension audit (continues T73 email-template a11y arc).
// 18.505 — ♿ Email a11y — `role="presentation"` added to 7 layout `<table>` tags across welcome-email + order-confirmation-email + quiz-nurture-email. Pre-fix every transactional email used `<table>` for layout (correct — flexbox/grid don't render reliably across email clients) WITHOUT the `role="presentation"` ARIA hint. Screen readers (and email-client assistive-tech overlays) announce these layout tables as DATA tables — "Table with 1 row, 1 column" — confusing the customer's experience of the email body. `role="presentation"` tells assistive tech "this is layout scaffolding, ignore semantics" so the prose flows naturally. WCAG 1.3.1 (info-and-relationships) hardening. Sister scc v13.6205 (7 same fixes) + GW v2.97.C0 (8 fixes — single emails.ts file, more layout tables). Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 73 dimension-shift to email-template a11y (round-3 candidate from T68 close memo). Hits-per-probe ratio: 22 across all 3 repos. Pure additive; no visual change in any client.
// 18.405 — 🛡️ NEW arc-guard `scripts/check-button-type.mjs` — pins T69 button-type sweep against future regression. Walks `app/` + `components/` for every `<button>` open tag. Fails build when both: (1) `onClick=` handler is present, AND (2) explicit `type=` attribute is absent. The combo is a strong signal the button is JS-handled (not the form's primary submit) — without explicit type, defaults to `type="submit"` per HTML5 spec, accidentally fires on Enter inside forms. Bare `<button>Text</button>` (no onClick) is allowed (typically intentional submit). 0/0 across all 3 repos post-T69 sweep. Wired into `pnpm check:button-type`. Sister scc v13.6105 + GW v2.97.B0 same-port (cross-stack symmetric). Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 70 — locks in T69's 313-button hardening.
// 18.305 — ♿ `<button type="button">` sweep — 50 button elements across 10 files. Pre-fix `<button onClick={...}>` without explicit `type=` defaults to `type="submit"` per HTML spec. INSIDE A FORM, pressing Enter while focused on any input fires the FIRST button without explicit type (or with type=submit) — meaning customers pressing Enter on a form might trigger an unrelated onClick handler (e.g. a remove button, a delete button, a "back" button). OUTSIDE a form, the default doesn't cause functional issues but it's still defensive coding. Sweep targeted only buttons with explicit `onClick=` handlers (clearly NOT meant to be the form's primary submit button). Python regex auto-inserted `type="button"` immediately after `<button` when both `onClick=` was present AND `type=` was absent. Sister scc v13.6005 (52 buttons / 11 files) + GW v2.97.A0 (211 buttons / 80 files — patient-portal admin / login / change-password / my-appointments forms had the most exposure). Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 69 button-type-default audit. WCAG 2.1.1 hardening + general defensive UX.
// 18.205 — 🌐 Robots meta — added Google SERP-display directives `max-snippet:-1`, `max-image-preview:large`, `max-video-preview:-1` to layout's robots.googleBot block. Pre-fix all 3 sites declared only `index, follow` — Google used conservative defaults: shorter snippets (~160c cap), smaller image previews, no video preview. With these directives, Google can render full-length snippets, large image previews (better for visual SERP layout — important for cannabis/dispensary search where customers scan for brand recognition + product previews), and full video previews. Pure additive SERP-visibility win — no functional change. Sister scc v13.5905 + GW v2.97.90 same-fix triple. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 65 robots-meta detail audit.
// 18.105 — 🛡️ NEW arc-guard `scripts/check-description-length-html.mjs` — sister of T63 title-length arc-guard, but for descriptions (160c HTML-rendered cap, no template suffix). Pins T6 + T62 fixes against future regression. Same brace + bracket-depth-aware reverse-walk pattern; only flags `description:` declarations that are immediate children of an exported `metadata` object. Same dynamic-skip rule (template literals with `${expr}` get skipped). 0/0 across all 3 repos. Wired into `pnpm check:description-length-html` (manual). Sister scc v13.5805 + GW v2.97.80 same-port (cross-stack symmetric). Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 64 — pairs with T63 to close the SERP-truncation arc on both title + description sides.
// 18.005 — 🛡️ NEW arc-guard `scripts/check-title-length-html.mjs` — pins T5 + T24 + T25 + T61 fixes against future regression. Walks app/, finds every TOP-LEVEL `metadata.title:` declaration (string literal or `{ absolute: }`), computes HTML-escaped rendered length (`&` → `&amp;` +4, `'` → `&#x27;` +5, `"` → `&quot;` +5, `<` → `&lt;` +3, `>` → `&gt;` +3) PLUS layout `title.template` suffix when applicable, fails if rendered length > 60 chars (Google's SERP cap). Brace-depth-aware reverse-walk only flags titles that are immediate children of an exported `metadata` object — skips array-of-object data structures (training step titles, FAQ items, breadcrumb chains) which don't render as <title>. Skips template literals with `${expr}` interpolation (dynamic — can't measure statically). Verified catch-rate via injection test: forced /blog title to "& Vendor Spotlights & More for Everyone" (2× `&` entity inflation) and arc-guard caught + reverted cleanly. 0/0 across glw + scc + GW (sister repos same script). Wired into `pnpm check:title-length-html` (manual). Sister scc v13.5705 + GW v2.97.70 same-port (cross-stack symmetric). Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 63 — closes the title-trim arc started at T5 and most recently bit at T61.
// 17.905 — 🌐 SEO title sweep — 3 over-cap pages caught via post-T29-50 re-audit. (1) /treasure-chest 74c → 56c (`&amp;` HTML-entity inflation in "& deep-discount" pushed body+template over 60-char SERP cap). title.absolute "Treasure Chest — Clearance Deals | Green Life Cannabis" baked in. (2) /our-story 74c → 56c (apostrophe in "Who's" → `&#x27;` adds +5 chars; body 47c + suffix 22c + entity 5c = 74c rendered). title.absolute "Our Story — Built by Everyone Here | Green Life Cannabis" drops the apostrophe-bearing phrase. (3) /blog 61c → 57c (`&` in "Guides & Vendor" → `&amp;` adds +4). Replaced `&` with `+` to skip HTML-entity inflation. Same bug class as `feedback_html_escape_inflates_meta_description_length` memory pin — measure HTML-rendered length, not JS source. Sister scc v13.5505 ports same fixes (treasure-chest + blog; scc has no /our-story). Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 61 cross-stack title-length re-audit (random-sample probe of sitemap URLs).
// 17.805 — ♿ /apply references-section inputs `autoComplete="off"` (T59 follow-up to T58 vendor-access). Pre-fix the 4 reference inputs (Name / Relationship / Phone / Email per reference, ×3 references = 12 inputs) had NO autoComplete attr — browser autofill could suggest the APPLICANT's own name/email/phone into a "reference" slot, creating confusing UX where users might accidentally submit their own contact info as their own reference. `autoComplete="off"` explicitly tells browsers + password managers NOT to suggest stored values for these fields. Sister scc same-fix. Note: the applicant's OWN name/email/phone (lines 473-498 in same file) correctly use autoComplete="name"/"email"/"tel" — that fix shipped earlier. T59 closes the references-section gap.
