// 17.505 — 🩹 Sitemap static-lastmod fix (Doug-action #3 closure). Pre-fix every static page (/about, /contact, /faq, /heroes/*, /community, /our-story, /visit, /find-your-strain, /press, /accessibility, etc.) stamped lastmod with `new Date()` — every sitemap render (every 30min revalidate cycle) emitted a "this page changed today" signal even though the actual prose content hadn't changed in months. Google sitemap docs: "lastmod should reflect when the content of the page last changed in a meaningful way" — wasted crawl budget on truly-static pages. New `STATIC_LASTMOD = new Date("2026-05-10")` constant — bump manually when static-page content actually changes (team-roster edit on /our-story, hours change on /visit, FAQ rewrite, etc.). 18 static-page entries swept; 11 remaining `new Date()` calls intentional (homepage = daily + sells "freshness" signal; /menu = live inventory; /deals = deals roll in/out daily; /treasure-chest = clearance lane turns daily; /near = dynamic town list; brand/deal/blog detail pages already use post.updatedAt or brand-page-specific dates). Doug-action queue #3 from earlier in round 2. Sister scc v13.5105 same-fix. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 55 sitemap freshness audit.
// 17.405 — 🖼️ CLS fix on Ray's Lemonade brand-hero image (`/brands/ray-s-lemonade-wa`). Pre-fix the marketing photo `<img>` was `w-full h-auto` with NO parent aspect-ratio class — browser had no way to know intrinsic dimensions before image loaded, so the box rendered 0px tall until paint, then jumped to full-size. Real CLS hit on a customer-facing brand page. Image is 1500×2100 (5:7 portrait, verified via curl + file). Added `width={1500} height={2100}` to the `<img>` — combined with `w-full h-auto` className, browser uses the intrinsic ratio to compute height = (containerWidth × 2100/1500) and reserves space upfront. Continues T34 CLS sweep — that fix shipped 3 of 7 sites (team-avatars on /our-story /community /about); this catches the lone non-aspect-parent variant. The remaining /deals/[id] + /treasure-chest + /brands/[slug] subbrand-logo + scc-equivalents were re-audited and are NOT bugs (parent divs have `aspect-square` or `aspect-[5/2]` reserving space; img inside w-full h-full is fine for CLS). Only the Ray's marketing photo had no aspect-parent. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 54 CLS sweep re-audit.
// 17.305 — 🛡️ Permissions-Policy hardening — added 9 directives to lock down browser APIs the marketing site never invokes: payment / usb / serial / bluetooth / midi / xr-spatial-tracking / magnetometer / accelerometer / gyroscope. All set to empty allowlist `()` = disabled for self + iframes. Defense-in-depth — blocks any future vendor JS / third-party widget from silently invoking these APIs (zero current use; pure attack-surface reduction). Specifically: payment=() prevents Payment Request API on a cash-only site; usb/serial/bluetooth/midi block hardware APIs; xr blocks WebXR; sensor APIs (magnetometer/accelerometer/gyroscope) block device-orientation reads. iHeartJane Boost iframe verified safe — Boost only needs private-state-token-* directives (already allowlisted; this set doesn't touch them). Sister scc v13.5005 + GW v2.97.30 same-fix triple. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 52 cross-stack Permissions-Policy hardening audit (post-T51 verification-tick saturation, dimension-shift to security-headers expansion).
// 17.205 — 🛡️ NEW arc-guard `scripts/check-per-route-og-image.mjs` + 7 MORE catches. Pins T48 + T49 fixes against future regression. Walks app/, finds every directory with a co-located `opengraph-image.tsx` file convention, checks the sibling page.tsx (or layout.tsx) for `openGraph.images: [...]` arrays containing known dead-code patterns: (1) `DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE` literal ref (T29-era SoT consolidation pattern), (2) `<x>.logoUrl` ref (T49-era brand-logo override), (3) `"/opengraph-image"` string literal (root homepage card path). First run on glw caught 7 MORE dead-code overrides T48+T49 missed: /about, /community, /deals (index — separate from /deals/[id]), /find-your-strain, /heroes, /our-story, /visit. All 7 had per-route opengraph-image.tsx files emitting custom 1200×630 cards but were dead code because page.tsx set `images: [DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE]`. Batch-fixed via Python with explicit per-route URL form (`/${route}/opengraph-image`). Sister scc v13.4905 (caught 5 more — same routes minus /deals + /our-story which scc doesn't have). Wired into `pnpm check:per-route-og-image` (manual) AND GW v2.96.X `pnpm check:all` build-gate. Cross-stack symmetric — same script ports cleanly to all 3 repos. Caught by /loop tick 50.
