// 17.005 — 🖼️ /blog/[slug] per-route OG image fix — explicit `images: [{ url: \`/blog/${slug}/opengraph-image\` }]`. Pre-fix `images: [DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE]` (which T29 introduced) overrode Next 16's per-route `app/blog/[slug]/opengraph-image.tsx` file convention — every blog post share-card on Twitter/Facebook/LinkedIn rendered the GENERIC homepage OG instead of the per-post custom card (which renders post title + category eyebrow + brand emoji). Per-route OG file existed + served 200 + had proper content but was DEAD CODE because the page metadata explicitly pointed at `/opengraph-image` (homepage). Verified pre-fix via curl: `<meta og:image>` was `https://www.greenlifecannabis.com/opengraph-image`, not `/blog/{slug}/opengraph-image`. Bug class: per-route file conventions in Next 16 only auto-inject when no explicit `metadata.openGraph.images` is set. Now: explicit per-route URL matches the file convention path. Sister scc v13.4705 same-fix. Audit: same fix may apply to /menu, /brands/[slug], /deals/[id] which all have co-located opengraph-image.tsx files — deferred to next ticks. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 48 cross-stack OG-vs-per-route audit.
// 16.905 — ⚡ /apple-icon.png cache rule path mismatch fix. Pre-fix `next.config.ts` had `source: "/apple-icon"` (no .png suffix) for the 24hr cache rule, but the Next 16 file convention `app/apple-icon.png/route.tsx` registers the route at the literal path `/apple-icon.png` (including the .png suffix per the directory name). Layout's `<link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/apple-icon.png">` matches the actual served path; the cache rule MISSED. Result: every iOS Safari Add-to-Home-Screen fetch + every iOS prefetch of the 180×180 apple-touch-icon hit the Vercel function uncached (`cache-control: max-age=0, must-revalidate` Vercel default) instead of CDN edge. Verified pre-fix via curl: `/apple-icon` → 404 WITH cache header (ironic — caching a 404), `/apple-icon.png` → 200 WITHOUT cache. Now matched: 24hr edge cache on the actual served path. Sister scc v13.4605 same-fix. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 47 cross-stack apple-icon cache audit (curl-verified mismatch).
// 16.805 — 🛡️ Suppress `X-Powered-By: Next.js` response header via `poweredByHeader: false`. Pre-fix glw + scc were the lone outliers across the 6-site stack — GW + cannagent + sureel + vrg all already suppress this header. Leaking framework identity helps attackers target known Next.js CVEs. Vercel emits the framework name but NOT the version, so the leak is "we use Next" not "we use Next 16.2.4" — minor but cheap defense-in-depth to close. Sister scc v13.4505 same-fix. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 46 cross-stack X-Powered-By audit (curl-confirmed glw + scc emit `x-powered-by: Next.js` while all 4 sister sites omit it).
// 16.705 — 🩹 /order → /menu sweep, 4 customer-facing surfaces. Continues T36 retraction theme: every customer-visible reference to `/order` adds a 307 redirect hop via proxy.ts. Caught 4 more sites today via cross-stack `<a href="/order">` audit on rendered prod HTML: (1) `components/SiteFooter.tsx` "Order for Pickup" footer link → /menu (label preserved — iHJ Boost is the cart UI). (2) `app/find-your-strain/StrainFinderClient.tsx buildOrderUrl()` — strain-finder result button built `/order?vibe=…&category=…&strain=…` URLs that proxy.ts 307'd to /menu AND dropped query params. Now points direct to /menu. (3) `app/page.tsx` HowTo JSON-LD steps positions 1+2 had `url: ${STORE.website}/order` — Google SERP HowTo-carousel clicks would have eaten the redirect hop. (4) `app/page.tsx` FAQ answer text "Build your cart on /order" → "/menu" (factually correct — /menu IS where the cart lives via iHJ Boost). Sister scc v13.4405 same-fix. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 45 cross-stack /order-href audit on rendered HTML.
// 16.605 — 🛡️ Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy `same-origin` added to next.config.ts response headers. Pre-fix glw + scc were the LONE outliers across the 6-site stack — cannagent + GW + sureel + vrg all served `cross-origin-opener-policy: same-origin`. Verified pre-fix via curl on all 6 sites (glw + scc absent; other 4 present). Note: GW v2.95.10 changelog claimed glw + scc had this header pre-T44; that note was wrong (likely confused glw + scc with cannagent during cross-stack port). COOP isolates this site's browsing context from cross-origin windows opened via window.open() — protects against Spectre/Meltdown side-channel attacks on shared memory + against cross-origin window.opener manipulation. Safe vs iHeartJane Boost: Boost uses iframes (not popups), and COOP only affects window.open() popup browsing contexts. CORP intentionally NOT set: marketing OG images need to be embeddable on Twitter/Facebook/Slack share-card crawlers, which would break under same-origin CORP. Pure additive — no customer-facing change. Sister scc v13.4305 same-fix. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 44 cross-stack COOP-presence audit (prod-headers-first methodology).
// 16.505 — 🌗 `colorScheme: "light"` added to viewport export — emits `<meta name="color-scheme" content="light">`. Pre-fix the meta was absent, so browsers' auto-dark-mode logic could re-tint form inputs, scrollbars, and default UA UI to dark on systems where the user prefers dark mode. The site is light-themed by design (cream/stone-50 backgrounds, dark text); auto-dark-tinting clashes with explicit Tailwind color classes — e.g. an input `bg-white` style gets coerced toward dark gray by Chrome's auto-dark engine, breaking contrast + readability. Declaring the supported scheme explicitly opts out. Sister scc v13.4205 + GW v2.96.X same-fix triple. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 43 cross-stack color-scheme audit (curl-confirmed all 3 sites missing the meta).
// 16.405 — 📱 `formatDetection: { telephone, date, address, email: false }` added to root layout metadata. iOS Safari auto-formats numeric strings (zip codes, prices, dates, addresses, WSLCB license numbers) as tap-callable / tap-mail / tap-date by default — body text becomes peppered with auto-tap-targets that, on click, open the dialer or Maps or Calendar instead of doing nothing or scrolling. Customer trying to highlight an address may accidentally trigger Maps; tapping a 5-digit zip code may dial it. We already use explicit `<a href="tel:…">` for the actual phone (3+ hits per page), so disabling auto-detection sitewide is pure UX cleanup with no loss of functionality. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 42 cross-stack format-detection audit (curl-confirmed all 3 sites missing the meta tag). Sister scc v13.4105 + GW v2.96.50 same-tick triple. Pure additive.
// 16.305 — ⚡ Preconnect to iHeartJane Boost origins on /menu — boost-assets.iheartjane.com (Boost JS bundle), api.iheartjane.com (REST + WebSocket cable), search.iheartjane.com (Algolia index). /menu's LCP is the first product card rendered from inside the Boost embed; pre-fix the customer paid full DNS+TLS+TCP RTT (50-300ms each) for each iHJ origin on first interaction. Preconnect at the page level primes the connection pool BEFORE the Boost JS even loads — saves the warmup roundtrips. Pure additive — `<link rel="preconnect">` doesn't change request behavior, just primes the connection. Pure compatibility-safe vs the Boost embed (this is what Google + Mozilla docs explicitly recommend for known third-party origins). Verified missing via cross-stack preconnect audit — glw + scc only preconnect to images.squarespace-cdn.com + static.wixstatic.com (brand-logo CDNs) but NOT to any iHJ origin. React 19 hoists `<link>` JSX in page-level returns to <head> automatically. Sister scc v13.3705 same-fix. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 40 cross-stack preconnect audit (prod-headers-first methodology continues to hold).
// 16.205 — 🛡️ X-Robots-Tag `noindex, nofollow` on /api/:path* responses. Defense-in-depth on top of robots.txt's `Disallow: /api/`. robots.txt blocks crawlers from FETCHING /api URLs, but if an API URL gets shared externally (Slack/Twitter unfurls, accidental copy-paste in tweets, email links), Google may still INDEX the URL without crawling it — SERP shows the bare URL with "No description available because of robots.txt." That's worst-of-both-worlds: SERP exposure of internal endpoint name + zero description. Header at response level says "even if you DID get here, don't index this." Verified via cross-stack curl audit — none of the 6 sites in the stack (glw/scc/GW/cannagent/sureel/vrg) currently set this header, glw + scc + GW shipping in same-tick triple now. Pure additive — no behavior change, no customer-facing effect. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 38 prod-headers-first methodology audit. Sister scc v13.3605 + GW v2.95.80 same-fix. cannagent + sureel + vrg follow-up pending.
// 16.105 — 🩹 Round-2 deep title+desc sweep glw side. /careers title 62→57 chars: swap ASCII apostrophe `'` (HTML-escapes to `&#x27;` +5 inflation) for typographic `’` (renders as Unicode directly, no escape). /visit description 161→145 chars: drop "directions" + "free parking" duplications. /deals/[id] entity-aware desc trim ported from GW v2.94.95 — pre-fix `rawDesc.length > 160` measured JS code units but Google measures HTML-escaped length, so /deals/heroes-20 came out 162 chars rendered (the `&` in "nurses & healthcare" inflated to `&amp;`). New iterative-shorten until escLen ≤ 160. Sister scc v13.3405 round-2 same-class deep sweep (different specific page hits but same /loop-uncovered-after-saturation pattern). Memory: feedback_html_escape_inflates_meta_description_length pinned this bug class earlier this session.
// 16.005 — 🌐 NEW `app/icon.tsx` — favicon-tier 32×32 PNG icon route. Pre-fix glw + scc emitted only `<link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" sizes="256x256">` + `<link rel="apple-touch-icon">`. Modern browsers prefer PNG > ICO + treat the 32×32 size hint as the canonical small-icon target — without the route, browser tabs fell back to a downscaled 256×256 .ico (decode quality varies by browser/OS, particularly degraded on high-DPI displays + on RSS readers / Slack-preview-card unfurlers that look at `<link rel="icon">` first). Cross-stack symmetric port — GW + cannagent + sureel + vrg all already have an `app/icon.tsx` file emitting Next 16's auto-discovered 32×32 PNG icon route; glw + scc were the lone outliers across the 6-site stack. Brand colors: glw bg=#022c22 fg=#a3e635 (matches manifest theme + body palette). 22-char `G` glyph centered. Verified missing via curl on prod homepage HTML — /icon route absent from glw + scc, present on GW. Sister scc v13.3405 same-port (S glyph on indigo). Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 37 favicon-completeness audit.
