// 15.405 — 🖼️ CLS fix: explicit width/height on team-avatar `<img>` tags across /our-story, /community, /about. Pre-fix browsers couldn't reserve image space pre-load (Cumulative Layout Shift hit on each card render — Core Web Vitals signal). Tailwind class `w-14 h-14` (56px) on /our-story + `w-12 h-12` (48px) on /about + /community guaranteed visual size, but HTML `width`/`height` attrs are required for browsers to compute the intrinsic-ratio space-reservation BEFORE the image loads. Now: `<img width={56} height={56} className="w-14 h-14 ...">` (or 48). 3 files swept (~10 team avatars). Used `<img>` rather than Next `<Image>` because photoSrc is null/optional + members.ts data is per-member opt-in (most fall through to initial-letter fallback divs). Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 34 CLS sweep — full audit found 7 `<img>` without explicit dims; the team-avatar trio was the easiest-to-fix subset (all had Tailwind size classes giving us the dimension knowledge). Other 4 (deals product, treasure-chest, brand sub-logo, ray's-lemonade hero) need per-image treatment.
// 15.305 — 🩹 [REVERTED at v15.905] SearchAction urlTemplate retargeted from /menu (broken) to /order (real). Pre-fix WebSite.potentialAction.target.urlTemplate pointed at `/menu?q={search_term_string}` — but /menu is the iHeartJane Boost embed, which renders the menu inline via JS but does NOT consume `?q=` searchParams. Google's Sitelinks Searchbox feature would have sent users to /menu?q=indica and they'd see an unfiltered embed (false promise to crawler + customer). /order is structurally identical from the customer's POV (cart-able product menu) but its OrderMenu.tsx reads `searchParams.get('q')` and seeds the search input — the actual search-result URL Google should target. Sister scc v13.2905 same-fix. GW (sister T33 ship v2.95.60) DROPPED the SearchAction block entirely since GW homepage has no `?q=` consumer + no equivalent /order page. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 33 SearchAction-target-actually-works audit.
