// 15.005 — 🖼️ og:image shape sweep across 20 page-level openGraph blocks. /loop tick 29 same-class as T19/T20/T21 shallow-overwrite (og:type / og:site_name / og:url) BUT on the `images` field shape. Pre-fix every page set `images: ["/opengraph-image"]` (string form) which emits ONLY `<meta property="og:image">` and OMITS `og:image:width`, `og:image:height`, `og:image:type`, `og:image:alt`. Verified via curl on /about prod: only the bare og:image meta tag emitted, none of the dimension/alt siblings. Without dimensions, share-card crawlers (Facebook, LinkedIn, Slack, Discord, iMessage) can't pre-allocate the share-card image area, falling back to small-card layout or "loading" placeholder until the image fetches. Without alt, accessibility readers + LinkedIn's accessible-mode can't describe the card. The layout already had the proper object-shape (`{ url, width, height, alt }`) but per-page string-form OVERRODE it via shallow-overwrite. Fix: NEW const `DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE` exported from `lib/store.ts` with the full shape (`url: "/opengraph-image"`, `width: 1200`, `height: 630`, `alt: "${STORE.name} — Cannabis Dispensary in Wenatchee, WA"`, `type: "image/png"`). Python sweep replaced `images: ["/opengraph-image"]` → `images: [DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE]` across 20 pages: about, apply, blog, blog/[slug], careers, community, deals, deals/[id], faq, find-your-strain, heroes, heroes/[cohort], learn, menu, near, near/[town], order, our-story, treasure-chest, visit. All now emit the full og:image:* meta tag set with proper alt for accessibility. Per-route `opengraph-image.tsx` overrides (e.g. `/menu`, `/brands/[slug]`) still win via Next 16 image-convention precedence — this default only kicks in where there's no per-route override. Sister scc same-push.
