// 14.605 — 🛡️ Permissions-Policy hardening: appended `camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), interest-cohort=()` to the existing private-state-token-* policy in next.config.ts. Pre-fix glw + scc were the lone outliers across the 6-site stack — cannagent + GW + sureel + vrg all had the camera/mic/geo lockdown; glw + scc had only the iHJ-required private-state-token-* directives. The new directives are orthogonal browser-API surfaces (no interaction with iHJ Cloudflare WAF trust-token verification) so the iHeartJane Boost integration on /menu is unaffected. Locks down browser APIs we never use (the marketing site never requests camera/mic/geo) protecting against any future vendor JS that might silently try. interest-cohort opts out of FLoC tracking. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop cross-stack Permissions-Policy presence sweep. Sister scc same-push.
