// 7.685 — 🏷️ %-off overlay on /devmenu + /order product cards (Doug 2026-05-08: "put the % off overlay on top of the product that is on sale similar to iheartjane"). Replaces the bottom-right "On Sale" chip (was UX_AUDIT_2026_05_03 P1-4 — sat too close to +Add and caused mistaps) with a prominent top-left red %-off badge that shows the actual discount magnitude (`20% OFF` or `$5 OFF` from `deal.discountType + discountValue`) instead of the wordier `deal.short` ("20% off flower"). At thumbnail scale a corner badge converts harder than a footer chip — the iHeartJane Boost embed on /menu uses this exact pattern, so customers already recognize it. Strain chip auto-displaces to bottom-right when a deal is present so corners stay non-overlapping (top-left = %-off, top-right = New / cart-quantity, bottom-left = weight, bottom-right = strain). Single-component edit at `app/order/OrderMenu.tsx` — fans out to both /order (native preview) and /devmenu (the wrapper at `app/devmenu/page.tsx` that imports the same OrderMenu). tsc clean.
// 7.665 — 🗺️ /order REMOVED from sitemap — caught via 200-or-bust audit (`grep loc sitemap | xargs curl`). /order is at priority 0.9 in sitemap but `proxy.ts` 307-redirects /order/* → /menu (per `feedback_customer_ctas_point_to_menu_only`: "Order CTAs → /menu, /order is dev-only"). Listing redirected URLs in sitemap wastes Google crawl budget — the bot must follow each redirect to find content. Same hygiene rule as the apex-www fix (v7.525): emit canonical destinations directly, no chains. When the native menu ships and proxy redirect is removed, /order can return to sitemap. Sister scc v8.805. tsc clean.
// 7.645 — 🔗 LocalBusiness @id graph-consolidation on /near pages — pre-fix each /near/<town> page declared a separate LocalBusiness entity at `${STORE.website}/near/<slug>#business`. Google's Knowledge Graph would treat each as a distinct store (chain branch) instead of merging the area-served declaration with the canonical home-page LocalBusiness at `${STORE.website}/#dispensary`. Now @id references the canonical entity and `mainEntityOfPage` carries the per-page binding. Net effect: Google sees ONE business with 18 area-served declarations instead of 18 phantom branches. Sister scc v8.785. tsc clean.
// 7.625 — 📰 Article rich-result eligibility — `/blog/[slug]` Article LD now includes `image` field. Pre-fix Article LD had headline/description/url/dates/author/wordCount but no `image` — Google's Article rich-result requires `image` to promote the post to article-card SERP styling. Without it the post just gets a normal blue-link result. Single-line `image: [\`${STORE.website}/opengraph-image\`]` addition. Sister scc v8.765. tsc clean.
// 7.605 — 🥼 OG image sister sweep — 4 more pages: /order, /careers, /heroes/[cohort], /blog/[slug]. Same Next 16 metadata-cascade quirk as v7.565: page-level openGraph fully replaces parent. Pre-fix all 4 share-previewed imageless on Slack/iMessage/Facebook. Verified live `curl /order | grep og:image` returned nothing pre-fix. Single `images: ["/opengraph-image"]` line per page. Pages with sibling opengraph-image.tsx (heroes-index, menu, community) intentionally untouched — Next auto-injects those. Sister scc v8.745. tsc clean.
// 7.585 — 🛡️ PII-leak hardening round 3: 2 sites in `app/api/track-install/route.ts` (auth lookup + audit insert). Pre-fix passed raw `err` to `console.error`. Auth lookup err can wrap Clerk SDK errors echoing the user object (email, fullName, emailAddresses[]); audit insert err echoes the audit-row payload (portalUserId, customerId, source). Sister of scc v8.725 same wave + v7.425/v7.485 prior PII-leak hardening. tsc clean.
// 7.565 — 🥼 OG image on /near pages — Next 16 metadata cascade quirk: page-level `openGraph: {...}` fully REPLACES parent's auto-injected images. Pre-fix `/near/<town>` + `/near` index pages had OG title/description/url/site_name but NO `og:image`, so Slack/iMessage/Facebook share previews rendered imageless. Single-line `images: ["/opengraph-image"]` reference on each metadata block — same pattern as `app/deals/page.tsx` already uses. 14 town pages + 1 index hub now share-previewed correctly. Sister scc v8.705. tsc clean.
// 7.545 — 🥇 apex → www sister sweep — 2 more sites: `lib/welcome-email.ts` + `lib/quiz-nurture-email.ts` URL fallbacks. Pre-fix both used `"https://greenlifecannabis.com"` as the vercel.app-defense fallback; apex 308's to www so every welcome-email "Find your strain" CTA + every quiz-nurture STOP-to-unsubscribe link redirected on click. Quiz-nurture matters most: CAN-SPAM compliance prefers direct-resolve unsub links (no redirect chain). Both now fall through to www. Sister of v7.525 STORE.website fix + scc v8.685 same wave. tsc clean.
