// 7.195 — 🚨 SOFT-404 fix: /blog/[slug] + /heroes/[cohort] now return real 404 for unknown slugs (was 200-with-not-found-content). Sister of scc v8.335. Caught while verifying new posts render — `curl /blog/nonexistent-test-slug-12345` returned 200 instead of 404. Body contained &ldquo;404&rdquo; + &ldquo;not found&rdquo; text but HTTP status was 200 (Next.js 16 default with `dynamicParams=true` + statically-generated routes). **SEO impact**: Google distinguishes real 404 from soft-404 (200-with-error-content); soft 404s erode adjacent paths' authority signal — every WP-era legacy URL not yet ported as a real post would have been categorized as soft-404 (200 + &ldquo;not found&rdquo; text → Google sees thin/error page on a real URL → de-indexes adjacent paths). Fix: added `export const dynamicParams = false;` to both `/blog/[slug]/page.tsx` + `/heroes/[cohort]/page.tsx` — only slugs from generateStaticParams() are served, all others return clean 404. /brands/[slug] LEFT alone (DB-backed dynamic — would break new-brand discovery). tsc clean. Verification next deploy: `curl -fsS -o /dev/null -w &quot;%{http_code}&quot; /blog/nonexistent-test-slug-12345` should return 404 (was 200).
// 7.065 — 🪞 Sunnyslope preposition fix on AI-citation surfaces — 3 sites the v6.945 sweep missed. Pre-fix `app/llms.txt/route.ts:113` + `app/llms-full.txt/route.ts:36` + `app/llms-full.txt/route.ts:83` all said &ldquo;same building **on** Sunnyslope&rdquo; — same drift class as v6.945 (Sunnyslope=neighborhood NOT street; the actual address is Center Road in Sunnyslope). v6.945 swept SEO descriptions in app/layout.tsx + app/our-story/page.tsx but the AI-citation route handlers were modified after-the-fact by another agent's linter pass and still had &ldquo;on Sunnyslope&rdquo; framing. AI search engines (ChatGPT/Claude/Perplexity) scrape these for citation context — pre-fix &ldquo;where is Green Life Cannabis?&rdquo; would cite ambiguous &ldquo;on Sunnyslope&rdquo; (could read as Sunnyslope Highway/road). Fixed: 3 instances `on` → `in`. Same memory rule (`feedback_address_ssot_check`). tsc clean.
// 7.045 — 🚨 SEO RECOVERY: Pre-Next.js legacy URL redirects — Wayback CDX confirmed 12+ legacy URLs crawled in 2024-2026 still 404'ing on the new site (Doug 2026-05-08: &ldquo;make sure we have all the old urls that were ranking this last month before the switchover&rdquo;). **High-impact catches:** (a) `/menu/products/:path*` — iHeartJane product detail URLs (hundreds indexed; each had unique SEO landing); (b) `/chelan-dispensary` — Chelan-area landing that ranked for &ldquo;Chelan dispensary&rdquo; queries; (c) `/my-account/:path*` — WooCommerce account paths (customers with old bookmarks would 404 looking for password-reset); (d) `/faqs` (note 's') — WordPress default FAQ URL; (e) `/feed` — WordPress RSS feed; (f) `/hello-world` — WordPress default first post; (g) `/gallery` — old photo gallery; (h) 7 sitemap variants (Yoast SEO emits multiple). All collapse to semantic equivalents — `/menu`, `/faq`, `/blog`, `/account`, `/sitemap.xml`, `/about`. **Why it matters**: every 404 on a previously-indexed URL drains link equity + trickle-traffic from long-tail Google searches. Wayback timestamps confirm these were crawled as recently as Wayback's 2025-2026 snapshot range (real customers + Google bots still hitting these). Sister sweep on scc v8.225 (43 URLs there — Seattle had a much longer WordPress era with hundreds of root-level blog posts). Cumulative pre-Next-cutover URL preservation arc. tsc clean. Verification: `curl -I /chelan-dispensary` should return 308 → /menu (was 404).
// 7.025 — 🚨 /llms-full.txt brand-voice violation: &ldquo;same family-style ownership has run ${'$'}{name} since opening&rdquo; → &ldquo;independently owned and operated since opening&rdquo;. Pre-fix the AI-citation long-form factual reference (`app/llms-full.txt/route.ts:85`) said &ldquo;family-style ownership&rdquo; — but per standing memory `feedback_brand_voice_sweep_state_2026_05_05` (Doug 2026-05-05): &ldquo;No 'veteran-owned' framing for Green Life — businesses are locally owned, not formally veteran-owned. Heroes-discount eligibility is fine; ownership claim is not.&rdquo; The same rule extends to family framing — earlier today shipped the same fix on glw v6.825 press story (`Family-run` → `Locally owned`) and v6.745/v6.765 cross-promo refinements. Critical because: this is a CUSTOMER-FACING AI-citation surface that ChatGPT/Claude/Perplexity scrape and cite as authoritative info about ownership claims when users ask &ldquo;is Green Life family-owned?&rdquo; — pre-fix the AI would answer &ldquo;yes, family-style owned&rdquo; (incorrect; brand-voice violation). Sister fix on scc v8.205 (parallel surface, same wording). tsc clean. Cumulative AI-citation-surface fix arc today: glw v6.805 (WSLCB# + veteran-owned in static llms.txt — turned out to be no-op since route shadows it), glw v6.885 (deleted dead-shadowed static), glw v7.005 (WAC misattribution × 4 sites), glw v7.025 (this — family-style ownership). The route handler at `app/llms-full.txt/route.ts` is the live SSoT for AI citations.
// 7.005 — 🚨 WAC 314-55-077 misattribution sweep — 4 sites incl. customer-facing AI-citation surfaces (`app/llms.txt/route.ts:122` + `app/llms-full.txt/route.ts:182`) plus `lib/seo-templates.tsx` (×2). Pre-fix all 4 cited WAC 314-55-077 as the source of the &ldquo;no medical claims&rdquo; rule — but 077 is the **traceability + audit-trail** rule (used correctly 14× in the inv repo for online-order count-confirm + manager-PIN audit + bag-mismatch). The actual prohibition on medical/health/efficacy claims lives in **WAC 314-55-155** (the advertising rules — false-or-misleading-statements clause). **Critical impact**: AI search engines (ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, Gemini) read /llms.txt + /llms-full.txt as authoritative regulatory citation context. Pre-fix, when a user asked &ldquo;what regulates Green Life Cannabis?&rdquo; the model would cite 077 as the source of the medical-claims rule — wrong rule attribution being citationally laundered through AI search. Same drift class as today's earlier llms.txt route-shadow catch (v6.885). **Fix**: 4 files updated to cite 155 for medical-claims; llms-full.txt also expanded the compliance-posture list with 105 (case cards) for completeness. Sister fix on scc v8.185 (parallel sites — same pattern). tsc clean.
// 6.985 — 🪞 /heroes page comment WAC misattribution — &ldquo;WAC 314-55-077 (no medical claims)&rdquo; → &ldquo;WAC 314-55-155&rdquo;. Pre-fix `app/heroes/page.tsx:15` code comment cited `WAC 314-55-077` as the source of the &ldquo;no medical claims&rdquo; rule. But WAC 314-55-077 is the **traceability/audit-trail** rule (used correctly in 14 places in the inv repo for online-order count-confirm + manager-PIN audit + bag-mismatch resolution). The actual &ldquo;no medical claims&rdquo; rule is part of **WAC 314-55-155** (the advertising rules — false/misleading-statements clause prohibits health/efficacy claims). The next line of the same comment correctly cites 155 for &ldquo;informational, not advertising-style&rdquo; — so the bug is just splitting one rule across two attributions. **Future-dev impact**: low — but if a future agent reads this comment and cites 077 elsewhere as the &ldquo;no medical claims&rdquo; rule, they'd be wrong in a regulator-facing context. Verified the correct WAC by surveying inv repo's 14 references to 077 (all traceability) + 71 references to 155 (advertising compliance). Single comment-only edit. tsc clean.
// 6.965 — 🪞 /press FACTS owner — "Verve Mgmt LLC · privately held" → "Verve Mgmt LLC · locally owned, independent". Pre-fix GLW press kit's owner-description used &ldquo;privately held&rdquo; framing while SCC's parallel field said &ldquo;Green Anne LLC · locally owned, independent&rdquo; (the brand-voice-canonical phrasing per memory `feedback_brand_voice_sweep_state_2026_05_05`). Both descriptions are technically accurate (Verve Mgmt LLC IS privately held — not publicly traded), but &ldquo;locally owned&rdquo; is the canonical brand-voice claim that customers care about (vs. the multi-state-operator chains). Asymmetric phrasing across press kits is also a journalist-quote-divergence risk: a writer pulling from both press pages would notice the framing difference. Fix: align GLW with SCC's canonical phrasing. Single-line edit. tsc clean.
// 6.945 — 🪞 SEO copy: "same building **on** Sunnyslope" → "**in** Sunnyslope" (3 sites). Pre-fix `app/layout.tsx:25 + :153` (SEO description meta) + `app/our-story/page.tsx:12` said "same building on Sunnyslope" — but Sunnyslope is the **neighborhood**, not the street (per memory `feedback_address_ssot_check`: "Sunnyslope=neighborhood NOT street"). The actual address is `3012 Center Road Ste A` — the store is IN Sunnyslope, not ON Sunnyslope. Sunnyslope IS a real road in Wenatchee (the road the neighborhood is named after, off the US-2 Sunnyslope exit), so "on Sunnyslope" can be misread as the address being on Sunnyslope Road — Google's local-business knowledge graph parsing this might confuse the canonical street, OR a customer Googling "Green Life Cannabis Sunnyslope" might drive on Sunnyslope Highway looking for the store rather than going to Center Road. **Fix**: changed preposition `on` → `in` for the 3 SEO/metadata sites where the phrase clearly refers to neighborhood-as-place. Other Sunnyslope references audited clean: "Sunnyslope side of town" (correct), "Sunnyslope exit" (US-2 highway exit name), "Right off Sunnyslope" (correctly references the road exit context), `areaServed` JSON-LD lists. tsc clean.
// 6.925 — 🪞 robots.ts disallow — added `/stash` + `/quiz/unsubscribe` to crawl-budget exclusions. Pre-fix `/stash` (per-visitor localStorage saved-products page) had `robots: { index: false, follow: true }` page-level noindex but was MISSING from `app/robots.ts` disallow list — search engines would still crawl it (wasting budget) before respecting the in-page noindex meta. Same drift class as the v6.785 /admin redirect crawl-budget fix. Sister fix on scc v8.165 (which also added `/rewards` since SCC has the SpringBig-cutover PWA but GLW doesn't). Each customer-facing page with `robots: { index: false }` should also be in the robots.ts disallow list — adding here saves the crawl request entirely instead of letting Google fetch the page just to read the noindex meta. tsc clean.
// 6.905 — 🚨 Real-page-vs-legacy-redirect conflict — /contact + /our-story unreachable. Pre-fix `next.config.ts:128` (`/contact → /visit`) + `:133` (`/our-story → /about`) — both shipped 2026-05-07 as &ldquo;legacy WordPress URL preservation&rdquo; with comment &ldquo;Verified 404'd on new site 2026-05-07.&rdquo; — but BOTH paths ALSO have real `app/{contact,our-story}/page.tsx` pages with full metadata + canonical declarations + structured-data + ISR-revalidate (the our-story page has `revalidate = 86400`). The 308-permanent redirect short-circuits BEFORE the page renders, making both pages dead code accessible only by direct URL typing — which gets 308'd away. **Customer-impact**: (a) `/contact` linked from `app/sitemap.ts:64` priority 0.6, `app/llms.txt/route.ts:69`, `app/faq/page.tsx:291`, `app/about/page.tsx:316` — every customer click on &ldquo;Contact us&rdquo; in FAQ or About lands on /visit (different page, different content), losing the structured contact info Doug wrote. (b) `/our-story` linked from `app/sitemap.ts` priority 0.7 — Google indexes /our-story but it 308s, eventually de-indexes; the team-history content + alumni list is invisible to search. **Fix**: removed both redirects from `next.config.ts`; kept the legacy-alias redirects (`/contact-us → /contact`, `/team → /about`, `/staff → /about`, etc.) since those don't have real pages. Bonus: pivoted `/contact-us` to redirect to `/contact` instead of `/visit` — now the legacy alias lands on the real contact page. Sister fix on scc v8.145 (same bug — /contact redirect + real page; SCC didn't have /our-story page so that redirect stays). tsc clean. Verification: `curl -I /contact` should return 200 once deployed (was 308).
// 6.885 — 🪦 Deleted dead-shadowed `public/llms.txt` (3KB static file). Major drift catch: `app/llms.txt/route.ts` (added v3.56 in the AI-search Phase 2 push) has been silently shadowing `public/llms.txt` (added in the original `c8afa77 GEO: beefed-up LocalBusiness schema` commit) for months — Next.js App Router serves `app/[file].txt/route.ts` over `public/[file].txt` at the same path. Verified via `diff <(curl /llms.txt) public/llms.txt` — completely different content (route has structured Quick-facts list; static had a single paragraph). My v6.805 &ldquo;fix&rdquo; to `public/llms.txt` (`413490 → 414755` + `veteran-owned → locally owned`) was a no-op — AI search engines see the route output, not the static file. Future agents reading `public/llms.txt` and finding drift will keep &ldquo;fixing&rdquo; a file that nobody serves. The route handler at `app/llms.txt/route.ts` is the SSoT — already has correct license + correct brand-voice + correct shop URL. Pinned a memory `feedback_llms_txt_route_shadows_static` so this doesn't happen again. Sister deletion on scc v8.125 (same dead-shadow pattern there). 1 file removed per repo.
