// 3.905 — `/accessibility` — WCAG link filter `levels=aaa` → `levels=a,aa` to match the surrounding 'WCAG 2.1 Level AA conformance' claim. Pre-fix the link text said "WCAG 2.1 Level AA" but the URL filter parameter `levels=aaa` filtered the W3C quickref to show ONLY Level AAA criteria — a level the page never claimed. Customer clicking expected to see what the store conforms to (A + AA cumulative) but landed on the enhanced AAA list which doesn't reflect our actual conformance. Post-fix `levels=a%2Caa` (URL-encoded comma) filters to A + AA — the cumulative criteria you actually have to pass for AA conformance per WCAG 2.1 § 5.2.1. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.665. tsc clean.
// 3.895 — `/accessibility` — DOH cannabis health-info link `/marijuana` → `/cannabis`. Pre-fix the link to "WA Department of Health" pointed to `https://doh.wa.gov/you-and-your-family/marijuana` which still loads via redirect, but DOH's canonical path is `/you-and-your-family/cannabis` (verified via WebFetch — breadcrumb reads "You & Your Family > Cannabis"). State has been transitioning away from "marijuana" to "cannabis" as the canonical term in regulation + public health surfaces. Updating the customer-visible source link to the canonical URL keeps the page from inheriting a future deprecation when the redirect eventually goes away. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.655. tsc clean.
// 3.885 — `app/global-error.tsx` — `aria-hidden="true"` on the decorative 😔 emoji wrapper. The catastrophic-fallback page (rendered when even the root layout fails) had `<div style={{ fontSize: '3rem' }}>😔</div>` — visually decorative but screen readers would announce 'frowning face' before the actual content. Adding aria-hidden lets assistive tech skip the emoji and go straight to the heading + recovery actions. Two-character a11y fix on a page that customers should rarely see, but accuracy still matters when they do. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.645. tsc clean.
// 3.875 — `/visit` hero — fix duplicate Tailwind breakpoint that dead-coded `sm:py-14`. Pre-fix the hero container had `py-10 sm:py-14 sm:py-20` (two `sm:` rules — last wins so it effectively rendered `py-10 sm:py-20`, skipping the medium step entirely). Post-fix: `py-10 sm:py-14 lg:py-20` — clean three-step responsive scale (mobile → tablet → desktop) so the hero gets the intended progressive vertical breathing room, especially on tablets in the 640-1024px range that previously snapped from py-10 straight to py-20. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.635 (same duplicate, same fix). tsc clean.
// 3.865 — `/community` plain-text email mentions converted to clickable mailto links with contextual subject prefills. Pre-fix the "Featured creators · Coming soon" + "Featured local businesses · Coming soon" blocks said "email <addr> with your handle..." / "Interested? Email <addr>." with the address as plain text — customers had to copy/paste it into their mail client. Post-fix: each STORE.email mention is wrapped in `<a href="mailto:...?subject=...">` with green-700 font-semibold underline + contextual subject ("Featured creator — interested" / "Featured local business — interested") so the inbox can route the inbound by intent. Companion to v3.685 mailto subject prefill sweep — closes the last two un-clickable email mentions on the public site. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.625. tsc clean.
// 3.855 — Order-confirmation email opt-out copy fix. Pre-fix the receipt said "to stop future marketing emails, reply STOP or email <addr>" — but "reply STOP" only works for SMS, not email (replying STOP to an email goes to nobody useful). Now: "email <addr>?subject=Unsubscribe" only. Email-clicked unsubscribe creates a clear inbound to the monitored address with subject pre-filled, easy to triage. HTML + plain-text variants both updated. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.595. tsc clean.
